The paper discusses simulation results for a machine learning algorithm, specifically constrained emphatic temporal-difference learning (ETD) algorithms. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the use of neural networks and reinforcement learning in ETD algorithms suggests the sub-categories of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and systems and control (cs.SY) may also be relevant. Finally, the paper discusses the behavior of the algorithms on example problems, which could fall under the sub-category of logic in computer science (cs.LO).
